{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "Added APIs to set skeleton node \\(bone\\) weights. The node weight determines how much influence a node has on the animation being played. \r\n\r\nUpdated the `actor_animation` demo with a key binding \\(`R`\\) to toggle the skeleton root node\u2019s weight between 0 and 1. When the weight is 0, you can see that the actor\u2019s hip \\(root node\\) is no longer updated when the animation is playing. \r\n\r\nNote that currently setting weight only affects skeleton animation that is not being manually updated through local skeleton transforms.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Added APIs to set skeleton node (bone) weights. The node weight determines how much influence a node has on the animation being played. </p>\n<p>Updated the <code>actor_animation</code> demo with a key binding (<code>R</code>) to toggle the skeleton root node\u2019s weight between 0 and 1. When the weight is 0, you can see that the actor\u2019s hip (root node) is no longer updated when the animation is playing. </p>\n<p>Note that currently setting weight only affects skeleton animation that is not being manually updated through local skeleton transforms.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Support setting skeleton node weights", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Support setting skeleton node weights</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "Added APIs to set skeleton node \\(bone\\) weights. The node weight determines how much influence a node has on the animation being played. \r\n\r\nUpdated the `actor_animation` demo with a key binding \\(`R`\\) to toggle the skeleton root node\u2019s weight between 0 and 1. When the weight is 0, you can see that the actor\u2019s hip \\(root node\\) is no longer updated when the animation is playing. \r\n\r\nNote that currently setting weight only affects skeleton animation that is not being manually updated through local skeleton transforms.", "links": {"decline": {"href": "https://ap